C-PTSD 
- covers all ages. For example, it could be acquired by anyone who is under the care of another, e.g. nursing home abuse, profound ASD, living in a warzone, natural disaster. d
- requires trauma to be repeated and uncontrollable
- may or may not have a stable caregiver relationship, but disruption to caregiving is not its focus

DTD
- must be acquired during the developmental period (ages 0-18)
- Diagnostic of an unstable caregiving relationship (caregiver is both the source of abuse and survival)
- Emphasises the effect of an unstable caregiving relationship on neuro- and psycho- development.


